      "content": "i get that both have points, but thats kind of a cop-out answer for a debate coach. if i have to present a winning case, i need to know which one has the stronger ethical foundation. like, is it more 'right' to prioritize the safety of a country's own people, or is the human right to seek safety something that should always override national laws? which one is the more solid moral ground?",
